annotationA: NAD-dependent protein deacylase Sirt4; NAD-dependent protein deacylase. Catalyzes the NAD- dependent hydrolysis of acyl groups from lysine residues
annotationB: Probable glutamine-dependent NAD(+) synthetase; ATP binding; NAD+ synthase (glutamine-hydrolyzing) activity; hydrolase activity, acting on carbon-nitrogen (but not peptide) bonds. It is involved in the biological process described with: NAD biosynthetic process; In the C-terminal section; belongs to the NAD synthetase family
